Using the steamer, he will then collect rubber on the upper Ucayali and bring it down the Pachitea to market.</p>
<p>

The story was inspired by the real life Peruvian rubber baron ; in the 1890s, Fitzcarrald did bring a steamship across an isthmus from one river into another, but it weighed only 30 tons and he had it dismantled before doing so.<physical_entity wordnetid="100001930" confidence="0.8">
